    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "The type analysis for type conversion actually will always convert array pointer to array ref since array inherits from ReferenceType. Therefore, the target type will be a reference, instead of a pointer which makes the assertion to be violated.\r\n@chriseth suggested me to add a branch to only allow bytes and string array conversion. I have added tests in the PR4904, this issue is fixed by adding the restriction. All code and the test are added to the PR.",
